The course concentrates on the ideas of the unity of the Finno-Ugric cultures. The overview will be given of the research history, lifestyles and contemporary sociocultural situation of the Finno-Ugric peoples that do not have their own independent states.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide students with an overview of history of investigation of Finno-Ugric peoples, traditional Finno-Ugric cultures, modern culture change, social and political development.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course student is able to compare different Finno-Ugric cultures, knows works of most important researchers of Finno-Ugric peoples. Student is able to analyze present-day situation of Finno-Ugric peoples.
